# Documentation Rules

## Documentation Strategy
- **Living Documentation**: Keep documentation updated with code changes
- **User-Focused**: Write for the intended audience (developers, users, stakeholders)
- **Comprehensive Coverage**: Document all public APIs, configurations, and processes
- **Accessibility**: Make documentation easy to find and understand

## README Standards
- **Project Overview**: Clear description of what the project does
- **Quick Start**: Simple steps to get the project running
- **Installation**: Detailed installation instructions
- **Usage Examples**: Practical examples of how to use the project
- **Contributing**: Guidelines for contributors
- **License**: Clear licensing information

## API Documentation
- **OpenAPI/Swagger**: Use standard API documentation formats
- **Interactive Examples**: Provide working examples for each endpoint
- **Error Codes**: Document all possible error responses
- **Authentication**: Clear authentication and authorization details
- **Rate Limiting**: Document usage limits and restrictions

## Code Documentation
- **Docstrings**: Comprehensive docstrings for all public functions
- **Comments**: Explain complex logic and business rules
- **Type Hints**: Use type hints for better code understanding
- **Examples**: Include usage examples in docstrings
- **Deprecation**: Clearly mark deprecated features

## Technical Documentation
- **Architecture**: Document system architecture and design decisions
- **Deployment**: Step-by-step deployment instructions
- **Configuration**: Document all configuration options
- **Troubleshooting**: Common issues and solutions
- **Performance**: Performance characteristics and optimization tips

## User Documentation
- **User Guides**: Step-by-step guides for end users
- **FAQ**: Frequently asked questions and answers
- **Screenshots**: Visual aids for user interfaces
- **Video Tutorials**: Video content for complex procedures
- **Support**: How to get help and support

## Maintenance
- **Regular Updates**: Schedule regular documentation reviews
- **Version Control**: Track documentation changes
- **Feedback Integration**: Incorporate user feedback into documentation
- **Quality Checks**: Review documentation for accuracy and clarity